Read-only sweep complete.

**Cadence**
`Game::runGameLoopOnce()` samples `Clock::frameTime()` once per main loop at [Game.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-
client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1090), calls 
`GameScheduler::alter(elapsedTime)` before render at [Game.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/cli
ent/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1134), then 
`IoWinManager::processEvents(elapsedTime)` at [Game.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/lib
rary/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1166), then `Graphics::update(elapsedTime)` at [Game.cpp](/D
:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1204). Objects 
scheduled for next frame are altered through `object->alter(elapsedTime)` at [AlterScheduler.cpp](/D:
/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedObject/src/shared/object/AlterScheduler.cpp:1239)
. So for these `cms_alterNextFrame` paths, yes: effectively once per render/main-loop frame, with 
`elapsedTime` available.

