**Door-lurch Answer**
Deny that line 602 alone is “the specific one behind the door lurch.” The inward pop is directly 
caused by the collision ray instantly pulling `m_currentZoom` inward at [FreeChaseCamera.cpp:691](/D:
/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/camera/FreeChaseCamera.cpp:691) 
or [FreeChaseCamera.cpp:739](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/c
amera/FreeChaseCamera.cpp:739). Line 602 is still a real bug: it is the fixed-per-frame recovery 
that makes the miss/recovery side converge much faster at high FPS, so it plausibly sharpens the 
pop-out/oscillation after the instant pull-in.
